WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.918
A living crust is powerful precisely because it grows and

2
00:00:03.018 --> 00:00:05.407
spreads on its own. But that is also the danger

3
00:00:05.507 --> 00:00:07.684
— it must never spread where it should not.

4
00:00:09.166 --> 00:00:12.954
Drop the bacteria in one spot. They multiply and diffuse outward across

5
00:00:13.054 --> 00:00:15.910
the sand — like a drop of ink spreading through water.

6
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.359
So we engineer a kill switch. Cross an environmental line — leave the target

7
00:00:22.459 --> 00:00:25.997
zone — and a toxin gene switches on and shuts the colony down.

8
00:00:27.466 --> 00:00:30.072
So two forces are always in balance: growth that

9
00:00:30.172 --> 00:00:33.173
builds the crust, and containment that keeps it exactly

10
00:00:33.273 --> 00:00:35.203
where we want it — and nowhere else.

